        <link href="https://www.citizenscienceuganda.info/consortium.html"/>
        <id>https://www.citizenscienceuganda.info/consortium.html</id>

        <updated>2019-07-30T16:07:14+02:00</updated>
            <summary>
                <![CDATA[
                    With ATRAP, HARISSA, D-SIRE and SWAMP, different academic partners from Uganda and Belgium collaborate on developing&hellip;
                ]]>
            </summary>
        <content type="html">
            <![CDATA[
                With <a href="https://www.citizenscienceuganda.info/atrap-project-description.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ATRAP</a>, <a href="https://www.citizenscienceuganda.info/harissa-project.html">HARISSA</a>, <a href="https://www.citizenscienceuganda.info/d-sire-project-description.html">D-SIRE</a> and <a href="https://www.citizenscienceuganda.info/swamp-project-description.html">SWAMP</a>, different academic partners from Uganda and Belgium collaborate on developing citizen science networks for data-collection on a variety of environmental risks. Beyond the goal to use citizen-generated data for their respective research questions, the projects will join forces to explore the potential of citizen scientists networks for communication and capacity-building in West and South-West-Uganda. Citizen Science networks for in-field data-collection on this scale, in thess context are rare and building-up this critical mass would not be possible without our partners, supporting institutions and of course, the citizen scientists.
            ]]>
        </content>
